.TH APF 8 "March 2026" "APF 2.0.2" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
apf \- Advanced Policy Firewall
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B apf
.RB [ \-s | \-r | \-f | \-l | \-t | \-e | \-o | \-v | \-h | \-\-rules | \-\-info | \-\-validate | \-\-la | \-\-ld ]
.br
.B apf
.RB { \-a | \-d }
.IR HOST\  [ COMMENT ]
.br
.B apf
.B \-u
.I HOST
.br
.B apf
.RB { \-ta | \-td }
.IR HOST\  TTL\  [ COMMENT ]
.br
.B apf
.RB [ \-\-templ | \-\-tempf ]
.br
.B apf
.B \-\-lookup
.I HOST
.br
.B apf
.RB { \-g | \-\-search }
.I PATTERN
.br
.B apf
.RB [ \-\-cc " [\fICC\fR | \fIIP\fR]] | " \-\-cc\-update ]
.br
.B apf
.RB [ \-\-ct\-scan | \-\-ct\-status ]
.br
.B apf
.RB [ \-\-ipset\-update | \-\-gre\-up | \-\-gre\-down | \-\-gre\-status ]
.br
.B apf
.B help
.RI [ topic ]
.br
.B apf
.RB { trust | cc | config | status | gre | ipset | ct }
.RI [ verb ]
.RI [ args ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Advanced Policy Firewall (APF) is an iptables/netfilter\-based firewall
management system for Linux servers.
It provides three approaches to network filtering:
stateful packet inspection policies,
trust\-based allow/deny host management with automatic DNS resolution,
and Reactive Address Blocking (RAB) for runtime policy violation tracking.
APF supports both IPv4 and IPv6, ipset\-based block lists, GRE tunnel
management, per\-IP virtual network policies, and temporary trust entries
with automatic expiry.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Core Operations
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-start
Load all firewall rules.
Uses fast load (iptables\-restore from snapshot) when available,
otherwise performs a full load.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-restart
Stop (flush) and reload all firewall rules.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-stop ", " \-\-flush
Stop (flush) all firewall rules and reset chains to ACCEPT.
.TP
.B \-\-rules
Dump all active iptables rules to stdout in
.BR iptables (8)
.B \-S
format (IPv4 + IPv6 when USE_IPV6=1).
Output is suitable for piping and scripting:
.B apf \-\-rules | grep DROP
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-list
View all firewall rules in an editor (pico, nano, vi).
.TP
.B \-\-info
Show firewall status summary: active state, rule/chain counts, trust
system statistics (allow/deny/temp entries, ban expiry, block escalation,
FQDN resolution), filtering configuration (stop targets, port lists,
packet sanity, connlimit, SYN flood, SMTP blocking), subsystem status
(fast load, RAB, VNET, Docker compat, ipset, GRE, remote block lists),
logging settings, and recent log entries.
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-st ", " \-\-status
Page through the full firewall status log.
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-refresh
Refresh and re\-resolve DNS names in trust rules.
.SS Trust Management
.TP
.BR \-a " \fIHOST\fR [\fICOMMENT\fR], " \-\-allow " \fIHOST\fR [\fICOMMENT\fR]"
Add
.I HOST
(IPv4, IPv6, CIDR, FQDN, or country code) to
.I allow_hosts.rules
and immediately load the rule into the live firewall.
.I HOST
may also be an advanced trust expression (see
.B TRUST SYSTEM
below) or a country code (see
.B COUNTRY CODE FILTERING
below):
.RS
.nf
apf \-a "tcp:in:d=22:s=10.0.0.0/8"
apf \-a "d=3306:s=192.168.1.5"
apf \-a US              # allow United States
apf \-a @EU             # allow all of Europe
apf \-d "tcp:in:d=22:s=CN"  # deny SSH from China
.fi
.RE
.TP
.BR \-d " \fIHOST\fR [\fICOMMENT\fR], " \-\-deny " \fIHOST\fR [\fICOMMENT\fR]"
Add
.I HOST
to
.I deny_hosts.rules
and immediately load the rule into the live firewall.
Also accepts advanced trust syntax and country codes.
.TP
.BR \-u " \fIHOST\fR, " \-\-remove " \fIHOST\fR, " \-\-unban " \fIHOST\fR"
Remove
.I HOST
(or country code) from all trust files (allow, deny, global, CC) and immediately
remove matching rules from the live firewall.
Accepts both bare hosts and advanced trust syntax.
Removing a bare IP also removes any advanced trust entries containing that IP.
.TP
.BR \-\-la ", " \-\-list\-allow
Display entries in
.IR allow_hosts.rules
(comments and blank lines excluded).
.TP
.BR \-\-ld ", " \-\-list\-deny
Display entries in
.IR deny_hosts.rules
(comments and blank lines excluded).
.TP
.BR \-\-lookup " \fIHOST\fR"
Check if
.I HOST
exists in any trust file (allow, deny, global allow, global deny, CC deny, CC allow).
Searches are case\-insensitive with line numbers shown.
Exits 0 if found, 1 if not found.
.SS Temporary Trust
.TP
.BR \-ta " \fIHOST\fR \fITTL\fR [\fICOMMENT\fR], " \-\-temp\-allow " \fIHOST\fR \fITTL\fR [\fICOMMENT\fR]"
Temporarily allow
.I HOST
with a time\-to\-live of
.IR TTL .
TTL may be in seconds or with a suffix:
.BR 5m " (minutes), " 1h " (hours), " 7d " (days)."
The entry is automatically removed when the TTL expires.
Also accepts advanced trust syntax.
.TP
.BR \-td " \fIHOST\fR \fITTL\fR [\fICOMMENT\fR], " \-\-temp\-deny " \fIHOST\fR \fITTL\fR [\fICOMMENT\fR]"
Temporarily deny
.I HOST
with a time\-to\-live of
.IR TTL .
Also accepts advanced trust syntax.
.TP
.BR \-\-templ ", " \-\-temp\-list
List all temporary trust entries with remaining TTL.
.TP
.BR \-\-tempf ", " \-\-temp\-flush
Remove all temporary trust entries.
.SS Diagnostics
.TP
.BR \-g " \fIPATTERN\fR, " \-\-search " \fIPATTERN\fR"
Search iptables rules (IPv4 and IPv6), ipset sets, and trust files for
.IR PATTERN .
Case\-insensitive.
.TP
.BR \-\-validate ", " \-\-check
Validate configuration without starting the firewall.
Checks stop targets, rate formats, connlimit syntax, and other settings.
Exits 0 on success, 1 on error with a diagnostic message.
.TP
.BR \-\-dump\-config ", " \-o ", " \-\-ovars
Output all configuration variables.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Output the version number.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show usage help and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-csf\-help
Show CSF\-to\-APF command mapping for users migrating from ConfigServer
Security & Firewall.
.SS Country Code Filtering
.TP
.BR \-\-cc " [\fICC\fR | \fIIP\fR]"
Show GeoIP country code filtering status. Without arguments, displays an
overview of all active country blocks with CIDR counts. With a country code
argument (e.g.,
.BR "apf \-\-cc CN" ),
shows detailed information for that country including continent, rules
status, cached data stats, and live ipset counts. Country detail works
even when filtering is inactive (no entries in rules files).
.IP
With an IP address or CIDR argument (e.g.,
.BR "apf \-\-cc 8.8.8.8" ),
looks up which country the address belongs to using cached GeoIP data.
Uses portable awk\-based CIDR containment for accurate matching.
On first lookup, downloads comprehensive world data (~1MB) for full coverage.
.TP
.B \-\-cc\-update
Refresh GeoIP data from upstream sources and atomically update all active
ipsets with zero downtime. Respects the
.B CC_INTERVAL
setting.
.SS Connection Tracking Limit
.TP
.B \-\-ct\-scan
Run a CT_LIMIT scan: read the conntrack table, count connections per source IP,
and temp\-block any IP exceeding the
.B CT_LIMIT
threshold. Requires CT_LIMIT > 0 in
.IR conf.apf .
Uses
.B conntrack \-L
when available, falling back to
.IR /proc/net/nf_conntrack .
Blocked IPs are added via
.BR "apf \-td" .
.TP
.B \-\-ct\-status
Show CT_LIMIT configuration, last scan timestamp, data source, and count of
active CT_LIMIT blocks. Does not require CT_LIMIT to be enabled.
.SS ipset Block Lists
.TP
.B \-\-ipset\-update
Hot\-reload ipset block lists from
.IR ipset.rules .
Lists are refreshed per their configured interval.
.SS GRE Tunnels
.TP
.B \-\-gre\-up
Bring up GRE tunnels defined in
.IR gre.rules .
.TP
.B \-\-gre\-down
Tear down GRE tunnels.
.TP
.B \-\-gre\-status
Show GRE tunnel status.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
APF supports a structured
.B apf \fInoun\fR \fIverb\fR
syntax for grouping related operations.
All existing single\-letter and long\-option flags continue to work as before;
subcommands provide an alternative interface.
Run
.B apf \fInoun\fR \-\-help
for verb\-level usage of any group.
.SS help \(em Built\-in Help
.TP
.B apf help
Show brief command reference (equivalent to
.BR "apf \-h" ).
.TP
.B apf help \fItopic\fR
Show help for a specific subcommand group (e.g.,
.BR "apf help trust" ).
Available topics:
.BR trust ", " cc ", " config ", " status ", " gre ", " ipset ", " ct .
.SS trust \(em Trust System Management
.TP
.B apf trust add \fIHOST\fR [\fICOMMENT\fR]
Allow a host (equivalent to
.BR "apf \-a" ).
.TP
.B apf trust deny \fIHOST\fR [\fICOMMENT\fR]
Deny a host (equivalent to
.BR "apf \-d" ).
.TP
.B apf trust remove \fIHOST\fR
Remove host from all trust lists (equivalent to
.BR "apf \-u" ).
.TP
.B apf trust list \fR[\fB\-\-allow\fR | \fB\-\-deny\fR | \fB\-\-temp\fR]
Show trust entries. Without a flag, shows all entries.
.B \-\-allow
and
.B \-\-deny
show only allow or deny entries;
.B \-\-temp
shows temporary entries with remaining TTL.
.TP
.B apf trust lookup \fIHOST\fR
Check if host exists in the trust system (equivalent to
.BR "\-\-lookup" ).
.TP
.B apf trust refresh
Re\-resolve FQDNs in trust rules (equivalent to
.BR "apf \-e" ).
.TP
.B apf trust flush \-\-temp
Remove all temporary trust entries (equivalent to
.BR "\-\-tempf" ).
.TP
.B apf trust temp add \fIHOST\fR \fITTL\fR [\fICOMMENT\fR]
Temporarily allow a host (equivalent to
.BR "apf \-ta" ).
.TP
.B apf trust temp deny \fIHOST\fR \fITTL\fR [\fICOMMENT\fR]
Temporarily deny a host (equivalent to
.BR "apf \-td" ).
.TP
.B apf trust temp remove \fIHOST\fR
Remove a temporary trust entry (equivalent to
.BR "apf \-u" ).
.TP
.B apf trust temp list
List temporary entries with remaining TTL (equivalent to
.BR "\-\-templ" ).
.TP
.B apf trust temp flush
Remove all temporary entries (equivalent to
.BR "\-\-tempf" ).
.SS cc \(em Country Code / GeoIP Operations
.TP
.B apf cc
Show GeoIP country code filtering overview (equivalent to
.BR "\-\-cc" ).
.TP
.B apf cc info \fR[\fICC\fR | \fIIP\fR]
Show detail for a country code or look up the country for an IP address
(equivalent to
.BR "\-\-cc CC" " or " "\-\-cc IP" ).
.TP
.B apf cc lookup \fIIP\fR
Look up which country an IP address belongs to.
.TP
.B apf cc update
Refresh GeoIP data and rebuild ipsets (equivalent to
.BR "\-\-cc\-update" ).
.SS config \(em Configuration and Validation
.TP
.B apf config dump
Output all configuration variables (equivalent to
.BR "apf \-o" ).
.TP
.B apf config validate
Validate configuration without starting the firewall (equivalent to
.BR "\-\-validate" ).
.SS status \(em Firewall Status and Diagnostics
.TP
.B apf status
Show firewall status summary (equivalent to
.BR "\-\-info" ).
.TP
.B apf status rules
Dump active iptables rules to stdout (equivalent to
.BR "\-\-rules" ).
.TP
.B apf status log
Page through the full status log (equivalent to
.BR "apf \-t" ).
.SS gre \(em GRE Tunnel Management
.TP
.B apf gre up
Bring up GRE tunnels (equivalent to
.BR "\-\-gre\-up" ).
.TP
.B apf gre down
Tear down GRE tunnels (equivalent to
.BR "\-\-gre\-down" ).
.TP
.B apf gre status
Show GRE tunnel status (equivalent to
.BR "\-\-gre\-status" ).
.SS ipset \(em ipset Block List Management
.TP
.B apf ipset update
Hot\-reload ipset block lists (equivalent to
.BR "\-\-ipset\-update" ).
.TP
.B apf ipset status
Show ipset list names and status.
.SS ct \(em Connection Tracking Limit
.TP
.B apf ct scan
Run a CT_LIMIT scan and block offenders (equivalent to
.BR "\-\-ct\-scan" ).
.TP
.B apf ct status
Show CT_LIMIT configuration and last scan info (equivalent to
.BR "\-\-ct\-status" ).
.SH TRUST SYSTEM
APF uses file\-based trust lists for allow and deny rules:
.TP
.I allow_hosts.rules
Local allow list (one entry per line).
.TP
.I deny_hosts.rules
Local deny list (one entry per line).
.TP
.I glob_allow.rules / glob_deny.rules
Downloaded global allow/deny lists.
.PP
Each entry may be an IPv4 address, IPv6 address, CIDR block, or FQDN.
FQDNs are pre\-resolved to IP addresses (IPv4 and IPv6 when USE_IPV6=1)
via
.B getent
before loading into iptables. Resolved IPs are stored in trust file
comments as
.B resolved=
metadata for efficient removal. Resolution timeout is controlled by
.B FQDN_TIMEOUT
(default 10 seconds). On refresh
.RB ( \-e ),
FQDNs are re\-resolved to pick up DNS changes.
Comments are supported as full lines beginning with
.BR # .
Inline comments on the same line as an address are not supported and will
cause that entry to be silently skipped.
The
.B apf \-a
and
.B apf \-d
commands automatically prepend a structured
.B # added ...
comment on the line before each entry.
.PP
Advanced trust syntax allows protocol, direction, and port filtering:
.PP
.RS
.B proto:flow:[s/d]=port:[s/d]=ip(/mask)
.RE
.PP
Both
.B proto
and
.B flow
are independently optional.
When proto is omitted, rules apply to both TCP and UDP.
When flow is omitted, rules apply to both inbound and outbound.
.PP
Examples:
.B tcp:in:d=22:s=10.0.0.0/8
(5\-field, inbound TCP 22 from 10.0.0.0/8),
.B in:d=443:s=192.168.1.0/24
(4\-field, inbound TCP+UDP 443),
.B d=3306:s=192.168.1.5
(3\-field, both directions, both protocols).
.PP
Temporary entries (added via
.B \-ta
or
.BR \-td )
include TTL and expiry metadata and are automatically removed by cron.
.SH COUNTRY CODE FILTERING
APF supports GeoIP\-based country blocking using ipset hash tables for
high\-performance matching. Country codes are specified in
.I cc_deny.rules
(block) and
.I cc_allow.rules
(permit), using ISO 3166\-1 alpha\-2 codes.
.PP
Continent shorthand expands to all countries in a continent:
.B @AF
(Africa),
.B @AS
(Asia),
.B @EU
(Europe),
.B @NA
(North America),
.B @SA
(South America),
.B @OC
(Oceania).
.PP
Simple entries block/allow all traffic from/to a country:
.PP
.RS
.nf
# cc_deny.rules
CN
RU
@EU
.fi
.RE
.PP
Advanced entries filter specific protocol/port/direction:
.PP
.RS
.nf
tcp:in:d=22:s=CN        # deny inbound SSH from China
tcp:in:d=25:s=RU        # deny inbound SMTP from Russia
tcp:in:d=22:s=*          # deny SSH from ALL denied countries
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B WARNING:
When
.I cc_allow.rules
has entries, it operates as a strict allowlist \(em
.B all countries NOT listed are implicitly blocked.
Adding even one country code locks the server to traffic from only the listed
countries. Ensure admin IPs are in
.I allow_hosts.rules
.RB ( "apf \-a YOUR_IP" )
before enabling, or use
.B DEVEL_MODE="1"
for auto\-flush safety during testing.
When both files have entries, deny takes precedence.
.PP
Country IP data is downloaded from public registries (ipverse.net, ipdeny.com)
and cached locally in the
.I geoip/
directory. Data is refreshed per
.B CC_INTERVAL
(default 7 days).
.PP
Configuration variables in
.I conf.apf:
.TP
.B CC_LOG
Log country\-blocked packets (requires LOG_DROP=1).
.TP
.B CC_LOG_ONLY
Audit mode: LOG without DROP. Useful for measuring impact before enforcing.
.TP
.B CC_SRC
Data source:
.B auto
(ipverse then ipdeny),
.BR ipverse ,
.BR ipdeny .
.TP
.B CC_CACHE_TTL
Hours before re-downloading cached country data on firewall start (default 24).
Set 0 to always download fresh data. Distinct from CC_INTERVAL (days).
.TP
.B CC_INTERVAL
Days between automatic data refresh via \-\-cc\-update (0 to disable).
.TP
.B CC_IPV6
Include IPv6 country blocks when USE_IPV6=1.
.SH VIRTUAL NETWORK (VNET)
The VNET subsystem creates per\-IP firewall policies for systems with multiple
IP addresses. When
.B SET_VNET=1
is set in
.IR conf.apf ,
APF detects aliased IPs on the untrusted interface and generates a
.I vnet/IP.rules
file for each one. These rule files can override global port filtering
variables (e.g., IG_TCP_CPORTS, EG_TCP_CPORTS) and include custom
iptables entries for that specific IP.
.PP
VNET is IPv4\-only. To create a per\-IP policy, copy the generated
default rules file and customize:
.PP
.in +4
.nf
cp /etc/apf/vnet/192.168.1.10.rules.default /etc/apf/vnet/192.168.1.10.rules
vi /etc/apf/vnet/192.168.1.10.rules
apf \-r
.fi
.in
.PP
The connection tracking limit scanner (CT_LIMIT) also supports per\-IP
overrides: set
.B CT_LIMIT=\(dq500\(dq
in a VNET rules file for a different threshold on that IP.
.PP
See
.B SET_VNET
and
.B SET_ADDIFACE
in
.I conf.apf
for configuration.
.SH CONFIGURATION
All configuration is in a single file,
.IR conf.apf ,
organized into sections:
.TP
.B Main Config
Development mode, install path, interfaces, IPv6 toggle, fast load, VNET,
FQDN resolution timeout, block escalation
.RB ( PERMBLOCK_COUNT / PERMBLOCK_INTERVAL ),
Docker/container compatibility mode
.RB ( DOCKER_COMPAT ).
.TP
.B Reactive Address Blocking
RAB enable/disable, sanity and port\-scan triggers, thresholds, timers.
.TP
.B Packet Filtering
TCP/UDP/ALL stop targets, packet sanity checks, INVALID state blocking.
.TP
.B Port & ICMP Filtering
Inbound/outbound TCP/UDP/ICMP ports, connection limits, SYN flood protection,
DNS resolution, P2P, multicast.
.TP
.B User & Application Filtering
UID\-based egress, command\-owner blocking, SMTP outbound restrictions.
.TP
.B Remote Lists & ipset
DShield, Spamhaus DROP, Project Honey Pot, ECN, global trust, ipset lists.
.TP
.B Country Code Filtering
CC_LOG, CC_LOG_ONLY, CC_SRC, CC_CACHE_TTL, CC_INTERVAL, CC_IPV6.
.TP
.B Connection Tracking Limit
CT_LIMIT (max connections per IP, 0=disabled), CT_INTERVAL (scan interval
seconds), CT_BLOCK_TIME (temp\-block duration), CT_PORTS (port filter),
CT_STATES (state filter), CT_SKIP_TIME_WAIT, CT_PERMANENT, CT_SKIP
(exempt IPs/CIDRs). VNET per\-IP overrides supported.
.TP
.B GRE Tunnels
USE_GRE, GRE_PERSIST, GRE_KEEPALIVE, GRE_MTU, GRE_TTL.
.TP
.B Logging & Kernel Tuning
Log targets (LOG, NFLOG, or deprecated ULOG), rate limits, sysctl tunables,
conntrack, helper chains.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
When set to any non\-empty value, disables ANSI color output in help and
error messages.
See
.UR https://no\-color.org/
no\-color.org
.UE .
.TP
.B TERM
If set to
.BR dumb ,
color output is also suppressed.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/apf/conf.apf
Main configuration file.
.TP
.I /etc/apf/allow_hosts.rules
Local allow trust list.
.TP
.I /etc/apf/deny_hosts.rules
Local deny trust list.
.TP
.I /etc/apf/glob_allow.rules
Global (downloaded) allow list.
.TP
.I /etc/apf/glob_deny.rules
Global (downloaded) deny list.
.TP
.I /etc/apf/cc_deny.rules
Country code deny list (ISO 3166\-1 alpha\-2 codes and continent shorthand).
.TP
.I /etc/apf/cc_allow.rules
Country code allow list.
.TP
.I /etc/apf/geoip/
Cached GeoIP country IP data (downloaded from public registries).
.TP
.I /etc/apf/ipset.rules
ipset block list definitions.
.TP
.I /etc/apf/gre.rules
GRE tunnel definitions.
.TP
.I /etc/apf/hook_pre.sh
Pre\-configuration hook script (inactive when permissions are 640).
.TP
.I /etc/apf/hook_post.sh
Post\-configuration hook script (inactive when permissions are 640).
.TP
.I /etc/apf/silent_ips.rules
Silent IP blocking list; drops all traffic to/from listed addresses with no logging.
.TP
.I /etc/apf/preroute.rules
Pre\-routing custom rules, sourced early in the firewall chain.
.TP
.I /etc/apf/postroute.rules
Post\-routing custom rules.
.TP
.I /etc/apf/vnet/
Per\-IP virtual network policy files.
.TP
.I /etc/apf/internals/apf_ctlimit.sh
Connection tracking limit internal library (sourced on demand).
.TP
.I /etc/cron.d/ctlimit.apf
CT_LIMIT scan cron job (created when CT_LIMIT > 0).
.TP
.I /etc/cron.d/apf
Consolidated cron: daily restart, hourly ipset refresh, per\-minute temp expiry.
.TP
.I /etc/logrotate.d/apf
Log rotation configuration for APF status and audit logs.
.TP
.I /etc/bash_completion.d/apf
Bash tab completion for apf command\-line options.
.TP
.I /var/log/apf_log
Default status log location.
.TP
.I /var/log/apf/audit.log
Structured JSONL audit log (config, service state, rule events).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error (missing dependency, invalid argument, lock contention, iptables failure).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B INSTALL_PATH
Override default install path
.RB ( /etc/apf ).
Must be set before running
.BR install.sh .
.TP
.B DEVEL_MODE
When set to
.B 1
in
.IR conf.apf ,
a cron job automatically flushes the firewall every 5 minutes to prevent
lockout during testing.
.SH EXAMPLES
Start the firewall:
.PP
.RS
.B apf \-s
.RE
.PP
Allow a host with a comment:
.PP
.RS
.B apf \-a 192.168.1.100 "office gateway"
.RE
.PP
Temporarily deny a host for 1 hour:
.PP
.RS
.B apf \-td 203.0.113.50 1h "brute force"
.RE
.PP
Allow inbound TCP port 22 from a subnet:
.PP
.RS
.B apf \-a "tcp:in:d=22:s=10.0.0.0/8"
.RE
.PP
Deny inbound port 3306 (both TCP and UDP) from a host:
.PP
.RS
.B apf \-d "d=3306:s=203.0.113.50"
.RE
.PP
Temporarily allow inbound TCP port 443 for 1 hour:
.PP
.RS
.B apf \-ta "tcp:in:d=443:s=192.168.1.100" 1h
.RE
.PP
Remove an advanced trust entry:
.PP
.RS
.B apf \-u "tcp:in:d=22:s=10.0.0.0/8"
.RE
.PP
Search rules for an IP address:
.PP
.RS
.B apf \-g 10.0.0.1
.RE
.PP
Dump rules to stdout (pipeable):
.PP
.RS
.B apf \-\-rules | grep DROP
.RE
.PP
Show firewall status summary:
.PP
.RS
.B apf \-\-info
.RE
.PP
Check if a host is in the trust system:
.PP
.RS
.B apf \-\-lookup 192.168.1.100
.RE
.PP
Restart the firewall after configuration changes:
.PP
.RS
.B apf \-r
.RE
.PP
Using subcommand syntax to manage trust:
.PP
.RS
.B apf trust add 192.168.1.100 "office gateway"
.RE
.PP
.RS
.B apf trust deny CN
.RE
.PP
.RS
.B apf trust temp deny 203.0.113.50 1h "brute force"
.RE
.PP
.RS
.B apf trust list \-\-temp
.RE
.PP
Using subcommand syntax for GeoIP and diagnostics:
.PP
.RS
.B apf cc info CN
.RE
.PP
.RS
.B apf cc lookup 8.8.8.8
.RE
.PP
.RS
.B apf status rules | grep DROP
.RE
.PP
.RS
.B apf config validate
.RE
